</div> 
<p><strong>Hand of Malenia</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Katanas" href="/Katanas" target="">Katana</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Hand of Malenia</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for Samurai Build and Bleed Builds.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Blade built into Malenia's prosthetic arm.</em><br><em>Through consecration it is resistant to rot.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Malenia's war prosthesis symbolized her victories.</em><br><em>Some claim to have seen wings when the weapon was raised aloft;</em><br><em>wings of fierce determination that have never known defeat.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Hand of Malenia in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Hand of Malenia weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Can be drawn by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enia" href="/Enia">Enia</a> out of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Remembrance of the Rot Goddess" href="/Remembrance+of+the+Rot+Goddess">Remembrance of the Rot Goddess</a>&nbsp;at the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Roundtable Hold" href="/Roundtable+Hold" target="">Roundtable Hold</a>,&nbsp;obtained after killing <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Malenia Blade of Miquella" href="/Malenia+Blade+of+Miquella">Malenia, Blade of Miquella</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Hand of Malenia Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Waterfowl Dance" href="/Waterfowl+Dance" target="">Waterfowl Dance</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li>Can't be enchanted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;nor boosted by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>Hand of Malenia</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Causes&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Hemorrhage" href="/Hemorrhage">Blood loss</a>&nbsp;Buildup:&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Hemorrhage" href="/Hemorrhage"><img title="Causes Blood Loss Buildup" src="/file/Elden-Ring/hemmorage.png" alt="hemmorage" width="18">&nbsp;(50)</a></li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;1000 <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Runes" href="/Runes">Runes</a></li> 
 <li>In order to get two of this weapon at the start of NG+, you can duplicate the remembrance and give one to <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enia" href="/Enia">Enia</a> for it before going to NG+ and one right after starting NG+, as you cannot use the same remembrance for the same reward twice on the same run.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
